The '''SS ''Argus''''' was a steel hulled ship lost on [[Lake Huron]] on November 9, 1913 during the [[Great Lakes storm of 1913]]. She was carrying a load of coal when she wrecked. She broke in two and sank with the loss of all 25 hands.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.regions.noaa.gov/great-lakes/index.php/highlights-archive/centennial_anniversary_storm_of_1913/shipwrecks-damages-casualties/ |title=NOAA |accessdate=2017-02-12}}</ref>
Portions of the wreckage were found by a local doctor along the shoreline at [[Bayfield, Ontario]] in mid-November 1913. <ref> {{cite news |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |title=Awful Marine Disaster on the Great Lakes |url= https://pubdocs.huroncounty.ca/weblink/3/doc/160063/Page1.aspx|work=The Signal |location=Goderich, Ontario |date=November 13, 1913 |access-date=April 19, 2018 }} </ref>
